folder: St. Edwards Street & Auburn Place, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: St. Edwards Street - Auburn Place
text:
St. Edwards Street, north from Auburn Place toward the Brooklyn Navy Yard. On the left, where Leo Place meets St. Edwards Street, is the Latte_sen shoe factory. On the right is Public School No. 67. The dwellings preceding the school were later razed and an annex added to the school.

All the buildings on the west side of the street were later razed, as shown in views 2 and 3, to make way for a new public housing construction. The shoe factory can be seen coming down in the later views, view 3 being north on Leo Place and shows also the public school and with its annex.

P. L. Sperr
View 1: October 31, 1937
View 2, 3: April 22, 1941

folder: St. Edwards Street & Auburn Place, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: St. Edwards Street - Auburn Place
text:
St. Edwards Street, at the N.E. corner of Auburn Place, showing the City Park branch of the Brooklyn Public Library. In the background is Cumberland Hospital; on the left Public School No. 67.
View 1: April 27, 1940
Views 2, 3: September 6, 1939

P.L. Sperr

View 2 shows the rear of the Library, seen from N. Elliott Place, and the J.J. Latteman shoe factory at St. Edwards and Leo Places.

Note: The factory and surrounding buildings were later demolished for the erection of Fort Greene Houses.
